Synchronization:

Data race: if 2 happen to perform the same/ similar actions: like incrementing the same variable- what really happens is
- read <var>
- update <var>
- rollback <var>

hence a race condition is happens.

representation in C :

// race.c
#include <pthread.h>
int counter = 0;
void * func(void * params) {
	counter++; // Non-atomic: READ → MODIFY → WRITE
	return NULL;
}
void main() {
	pthread_t thread1, thread2;
	pthread_create(&thread1, 0, func, 0);
	pthread_create(&thread2, 0, func, 0);
	pthread_join(thread1, 0);
	pthread_join(thread2, 0);
	// counter may be 1 instead of 2!
}


step 1: Compile with debug symbols
	$gcc -g race.c -lpthread -o race

step 2: Run under helgrind
	$valgrind --tool=helgrind ./race

-g to show line numbers on helgrind and adds debug info.
-lpthread : l= link, this links the exe file to the pthread library.


